}}{{TIDTOC|embedded}} ==Overview== The FCC photos depict the device with an ADMtek ADM5120, however, Edimax's specs list the device with a Realtek RTL8181. It is assumed that Edimax's specifications are in error..
"1246-00000022-010" is silkscreened on the wireless board. "1246-00000026-010" may be silkscreened on the main board.
The FCC test report lists the following items as identical.. *Edimax EW-7206Cg *GLP GP-105Ug *GLP GAP-E06Cg
Possible 00:50:FC ('''[[Edimax]]''') OUI (in FCC manual web UI screenshots)
